				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: /tgb on bards<a name="55151"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 4 04 4:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>/tgb is disabled for bards because a high level bard could PL a whole group with haste, mana, regen, ds, or whatever you really wanted and could stay outside the group and the group would get XP.
<br />

<br />
We got AE songs instead of Mass Group Buff, because then we could pulse DA on a whole raid.  Imagine raids with 30 bards with MGB so when things went sour you could get 2-3 to chain-DA so that not only the clerics could camp, but the whole surviving raid force.
<br />

<br />
Really, DA would be the only use for MGB that I could see.  with our songs being so short we couldn't keep it up long enough to be worth it.  Maybe if you were the only bard and the fight was quick you could hit the raid with 18 secs of overhaste or resist, but then its gone.  maybe with 49 selos if you needed to get a lot of people somewhere quick.
<br />

<br />
Imagine how ticked people would be if you could MGB shadowstep <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /></span></td>
